---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — SHR7"
  description="How SHR7 handles data: what we collect for link analytics, cookies, and third-party advertising via Google AdSense."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated: 2026</p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What we collect</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      When you create a short link we store the destination URL, the generated
      code and a creation timestamp. When someone visits a short link we record
      the time of the click, the referring website's hostname, and the
      visitor's country (derived from Cloudflare's network). We do not store IP
      addresses or any personally identifying information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Cookies & advertising</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      This site is supported by advertising. We use Google AdSense, which may
      use cookies and similar technologies to serve and personalise ads based
      on your prior visits to this and other websites. You can learn more and
      manage your preferences at
      <a class="text-clay-500 underline" href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        Google's Ads policy
      </a>. SHR7 itself does not set tracking cookies.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Data retention</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      Link and click data is retained to provide the statistics feature. Please
      do not use SHR7 to shorten links that contain sensitive information, as
      short links are publicly accessible by anyone who has the code.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      Questions about this policy? Reach out via the contact details on your
      deployment.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
